# xdg-desktop-portal exposes a D-Bus interface (org.freedesktop.portal.Settings)
# that Electron apps (VS Code, Obsidian, Discord) and libadwaita apps use to read
# the system color-scheme preference (prefer-dark/prefer-light).
# xdg-desktop-portal-gtk is the GTK backend that bridges gsettings/dconf values
# to the portal, so when toggle-color sets org.gnome.desktop.interface color-scheme
# via gsettings, the portal picks it up and notifies apps over D-Bus.
#
# Both services are D-Bus activated — systemd starts them on demand when an app
# first queries the portal, no manual enable/start needed. This is Claude's claim 
# so if something isn't working, double check it.
xdg-desktop-portal
xdg-desktop-portal-gtk

